Gold fell from a record high in
after-hours trading on the Comex, and silver futures slipped
from the highest price in 30 years.  Gold futures for December delivery were trading at
$1,388.40 an ounce as of 4:02 p.m. in New York, after touching a
record $1,424.30. Earlier, the contract had settled at
$1,410.10, up $6.90, or 0.5 percent, from yesterdayâ€™s close.  Silver futures for December delivery were at $26.77 an
ounce. Earlier, the contract settled at $28.906 on the Comex, up
5.4 percent, after touching $29.34, the highest price for a
most-active contract since March 1980.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
